    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-17T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-17T18:00:00-05:00" n="982"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d982">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.515/7–1745: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 982<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_KGF1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kennan</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">u. s. urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-17T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 17, 1945—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1629. British have now agreed to proposal outlined <gloss target="#t_Deptstel1"
                        >Deptstel</gloss> 1316 June 15.<note n="1" xml:id="d982fn1">See <ref
                            target="frus1945Berlinv01#d382fn1">vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>,
                            document No. 382, footnote 1</ref>.</note> Spanish situation urgent.
                        <gloss target="#t_reurtel1">Reurtel</gloss> 2570 July 14<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d982fn2">
                        <ref target="frus1945Berlinv01#d326">Document No. 326, printed in vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> inform Soviet we assume their concurrence in view of reports
                    from Ankara and Stockholm that Soviet has so warned Turks and Swedes. Make point
                    5 of <gloss target="#t_Depstel1">Depstel</gloss> 1534 July 6<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d982fn3">See <ref target="frus1945Berlinv01#d383fn1">vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, document No. 383, footnote 1</ref>.</note>
                    if can conveniently do so. For your information <gloss target="#t_Dept1"
                        >Dept</gloss> proposes to continue stressing coordinated action and
                    maintenance of trusteeship principle. This would preclude particular occupying
                    power from disposing of German external assets to its own advantage. American
                    expressions to Soviet regarding German Legation property Stockholm and German
                    shares Rumanian oil companies will probably make these points.</p>
                <p>Sent to Moscow, repeated to <gloss target="#t_SecState1">SecState</gloss> Berlin
                    for <persName corresp="#p_CEG1">Collado</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_DE2">Despres</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GJC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                        </persName>
                        <lb/>
                        <persName corresp="#p_OCT1">C[ovey] T. O[liver]</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
